<br>
I mean, if I rape a girl the cops aren't gonna broadcast 24/7 what evidence they have on me and exactly where they believe I am and when they expect to arrest me.  <br>
<br>
Hindsight, we were dead on who was behind it and where they were.  We didn't make a first move for a month, even tho we had our fingers pointed at and were requesting assistance from the Afgan govt.  <br>
<br>
&quot;with us or against us&quot; isn't 'fight with us or be attacked by us'.   If we have evidence of terrorists in a country, and that country doesn't take sides (ie, leaves the terrorists alone but doesn't &quot;support&quot; them), what are we supposed to do?  Forget about it?  <br>
<br>
War is a crappy solution.  It should always be the LAST solution.  Sometimes it's the only solution.  <br>
<br>
Bring up WWII again.  Can I assume you are against the allied powers aggression against germany... we bombed thier cities and took over their concentration camps and all... why?  were we justified in killing those germans and disrupting thier way of life so?   WWII was horrible, nobody wanted to be involved, we stayed out of it for so long partially because we didn't want to interfere with other soverienty and because we simply don't want to fight wars if there are other options.  But check your history books, Europe *tried* diplomacy for a good while with Nazi Germany, they even all but gave up a country (poland I believe) to them to avoid escalating conflict.  We were ready to sign a nonaggression treaty with Japan before they bombed pearl harbor.<br>
<br>
If someone is determined to kill you, you have two options.  Die, or kill him.  If you run he can chase you.  If you try to talk, sign papers, tell him you love him in spite of your differences, he'll still kill you.   Very few lethal conflicts are a result of 2 sides who both want to fight.   The concept of 'call the police' doesn't apply in international relations, there is no police.  The UN has no power to stop anyone, and with terrorists you don't even have a political body to be at odds with. <br>
<br>
The only &quot;good&quot; thing you could possibly walk away from in this situation we have is we hit the breaking point before those lunatics used a nuke or serious biological weapon.   The chances of it happening now vs a year ago are SIGNIFICANTLY reduced.<br>
<br>
The thing getting me about the prisoners now is it's not a basic checkup on us, it's a media circus... playing as if these assholes are the victims in all of this.  Now, if you wanna talk the hundreds of suspects that have been detained since 9/11 within the US, you got a big grey area... that is a very tough balance of civil rights and defense of life.  These POW's from afganistan are not.  They are the enemy, period.  They have shown a strong tendency and aptitude to revolt and kill while being detained as prisoners.  They are being treated a HELL of a lot better than they had treated their own people.  The US government isn't banning anyone from checking up on thier treatmetn, it's a total non issue.<br>
